oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Crab Orchard Inn
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the exterior of the Crab Orchard Inn, which was built in 1823 by enslaved people using bricklayers from Knoxville. Robert Burke had owned the inn for most of its tenure until it burned in a fire around 1929.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Taverns (Inns); Historic buildings
